ASSOCIATE DIRECTOR – MEDICINAL CHEMISTRY
Your responsibilities will consist mainly of leading and managing the medicinal chemistry, ADMET/PK and all related aspects of small molecule drug discovery programs in lead identification and especially lead optimization stages in order to deliver (pre-)clinical candidates. You will manage a team of (medicinal) chemists (internal and external) and will report to the Director of Medicinal Chemistry.
Profile:

You hold an academic degree in Chemistry, Pharmacy or equivalent and  a PhD degree preferentially in Chemistry or Pharmaceutical Sciences, with as subject the synthesis of small organic molecules;
You have solid knowledge and experience in Medicinal Chemistry (design and synthesis) and a good knowledge and understanding of in vitro ADMET/PK;
Previous experience in a pharma/biotech company as medicinal chemist in a leadership position for lead optimization programs is a requirement;
You are familiar with IP and can propose IP strategies based on experimental data and prior art constrains;
You have a strong interest in scientific research and more specifically in research towards new medicines;
You are goal oriented and can handle deadlines and pressure;
You are a team player who can operate independently and are quality and accuracy oriented;
You are used to interact with external collaborators, partners or CROs in the field of chemistry, ADMET, in vitro and in vivo pharmacology;
You are communicative and fluent in English; knowledge of Dutch or French is an asset.

Offer :
Employment contract of unlimited duration.
Competitive salary package.
