Anhui Agricultural University's Implementing Measures of High-level Talents Introduction
TTo conscientiously implement Anhui Agricultural University (AAU)'s strategy of strengthening by talents, perfect AAU's talents introduction mechanism, and to enhance AAU faculty's teaching level, AAU's Department of Personnel decides to formulate new measures of talents introduction in close accordance with AAU's "12th Five Year " development program and talents planning.
 
I. Positions for Introduction
According to the needs of discipline development, academic levels, scientific research and teaching, the positions for introduction are:
1. State key or provincial/ministerial-level key disciplines, key laboratories and research bases.
2. The doctoral degree programs and master degree programs needed to be strengthened or improved, and those emerging or key disciplines of priority.
3. Important basic disciplines significant to the cultivation of students' basic theory and practice skills.
II. Types of Talents to Be Introduced
Those high-level talents to be introduced must support the leadership of the Communist Party of China, love China, must have good professional ethics and teamwork spirit, have good health and a certain level of the leadership and management.
1. Academicians of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, or of Chinese Academy of Engineering;
2. National key discipline leaders, winners of the National Outstanding Youth Fund, winners of COD（the Central Organization Department）"Thousand People Program", or chair professors of MOE（the Ministry of Education）"Cheung Kong Scholars Program",generally aged under 50;
3. Special professors of Anhui Province "Wanjiang Scholars Award Program" or winners of "Hundred Talents Program", generally aged under 45;
4. AAU special professors, chair Professors, generally aged under 45;
5. Professors or professionals of full professorship, generally aged under 45;
6. Associate professors with doctoral degrees, or application-type talents in engineering and breeding, or PhDs and postdoctoral fellows from famous overseas universities, generally aged under 40;
7. Urgently needed doctors for discipline construction, generally aged under 35. 
III. Treatment for the Introduced Talents
1. Academicians of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, or of the Chinese Academy of Engineering;
(1) research start-up fund of RMB3000,000 yuan;
(2) a property flat of 200 m2 ;
(3) annual allowance of RMB1000,000 yuan;
(4) research assistant echelon, and special offers for international researches or communication etc;
(5) spouse job transfer.
2. National key discipline leaders, winners of "National Outstanding Youth Science Foundation", winners of COD "Thousand People Program" or of MOE "Cheung Kong Scholars Program":
(1) research start-up fund of RMB2000,000 yuan for natural sciences, or RMB 500,000 yuan for social sciences;
(2) a property flat of 140 m2;
(3) annual allowance of RMB 300，000--500，000 yuan;
(4) research assistants, studios and necessary facilities;
(5) spouse job transfer.
3. Special professors of "Wanjiang Scholars Award Program", or of Anhui Province "Hundred Talents Program":
(1) research start-up fund of RMB500,000-1000,000 yuan for natural sciences, or RMB200,000-500,000yuan for social sciences;
(2) a property flat of 110 m2 , or special subsidy of RMB500,000 yuan for house purchase;
(3) annual allowance of RMB200，000--300，000 yuan;
(4) research assistants, studios and necessary facilities;
(5) negotiable spouse job transfer in line with our work needs and the spouse's specific skills.
4. Anhui Agriculture University special professors or chair professors:
AAU special professors refer to the professors who can work full-time or for more than six months per year in AAU.
(1) research start-up fund of RMB400,000-800,000yuan for natural sciences, or RMB100,000-300,000yuan for social sciences;
(2) annual allowance of RMB100，000--200，000 yuan;
(3) a property flat of 90 m2 (required to complete a certain service period), or special subsidy of RMB400,000yuan for house purchase;
(4) necessary research assistants, studios and facilities (related expenses included in AAU's scientific research start-up fund);
(5) negotiable spouse job transfer in line with our work needs and the spouse’s specific skills.
Anhui Agricultural University chair professors: AAU chair professors have to work no less than 2 months per year in AAU. Monthly living allowance of RMB20,000-30,000yuan and a 70 m2 apartment shall be offered according to their actual working months in AAU, but no wages or other benefits.
(1) research start-up fund of RMB200,000-400,000yuan for natural sciences, or RMB50,000-100,000yuan for social sciences; (2) studios and necessary facilities; (3) special offer to overseas professors for an international trip per year.
5. Professors or professionals of full professorship:
(1) research start-up fund of RMB200,000-300,000yuan for natural sciences, or RMB50,000-200,000 yuan for social sciences;
(2) a flat of 90 m2, or special subsidy of RMB300,000yuan for house purchase (including settling-in allowance);
