6. Associate professors with doctorate, brilliant application-type talents in engineering or breeding, and doctors and postdoctoral fellows from famous overseas universities.
(1) research start-up fund of RMB100,000-200,000yuan for natural sciences, or RMB50,000-100,000yuan for social sciences;
(2) special subsidy of RMB200,000yuan for house purchase;
(3) necessary studios and labs;
(4) negotiable spouse job transfer (if meeting AAU job demands) for those recognized excellent by AAU.
7. Urgently-needed doctors for specialty or discipline construction:
(1) low-rent interim flat (six years), or RMB1200 yuan per month for rent subsidy (6 years), or one-time subsidy of RMB150,000 yuan for house purchase (house purchase contract required);
(2) one-time setting-in allowance of RMB50,000 yuan;
(3) research start-up fund (in the form of project financing, the same below): RMB60,000 yuan for natural sciences, or RMB20,000 yuan for social sciences.
Treatment for other types (doctors)
(1) a low-rent interim flat (six years), or RMB1000 yuan per month for rent subsidy (6 years), or one-time subsidy of RMB 100,000 yuan for house purchase (house purchase contract required);
(2) one-time setting-in allowance of RMB30,000 yuan.
(3) research start-up fund (in the form of project financing, the same below): RMB 30,000yuan for natural sciences, or RMB 10,000yuan for social sciences.
IV. Procedure of Talents Introduction
1. Plan making
Introduction plans are first made by AAU's sub-colleges or other units according to their needs for faculty or discipline construction, and are carried out only after the validation by AAU authorities. And the plans'completion is to be a factor for the year-end assessment of the colleges’ work by AAU.
2. Preliminary examination
The employers must first obtain the concerned personal materials from the high-level talents who have the intention to work for AAU, including their representative papers and works, award certificates, degree certificates, professional and technical qualifications, resumes, and information about their spouses and children, and help them to fill in "High-level Talents Application Form for Introduction by Anhui Agricultural University", next submit the materials to AAU's Department of Personnel, which shall turn to experts for examination of the materials by letter, and then, in conjunction with the employing units, interview the applicants, and put forward preliminary suggestions.
3. Review
AAU has set up a high-level talents-introduction leading group, which, headed by the president, comprises the leaders of Department of Personnel, Department of Science and Technology, Office of Educational Administration, Department of Development and Planning, Graduate School, Commission for Discipline Inspection, and experts from AAU Academic Committee; the Department of Personnel, responsible for the group's daily work, has to submit the applicants'materials to the group for audit and comprehensive evaluation. Last, the group, in accordance with "Anhui Agricultural University (Replacing Grading by Appointment) Employment Qualifications about Teachers'Professional and Technical Positions "(for Trial Implementation)" (AAU Personnel [2010] No.22) and the applicants'personal achievements，shall decide on the applicants'professional or technical posts if qualified.
4. Agreement signing
Department of Personnel shall, on behalf of AAU, sign an agreement with those applicants qualified for introduction.
V. Administration of the Introduced Talents 
1. The introduced high-level talents have to sign on“Anhui Agricultural University Agreements with Introduced High-level Talents", and have to serve AAU for no less than eight years in compliance with "Anhui Agricultural University Temporary Provisions on the Service Period of Employees", and therefore in the service years, AAU shall in principle refuse any application for resignation, job transfers, or going abroad at their own charge. AAU shall deal with the unapproved leaving in line with its relevant provisions and signed agreements.
2. Procedure of scientific research funding
The introduced high-level talents must first present their applications and fill out "Research Funding Application of Anhui Agricultural University Introduced High-level Talents", and then submit the applications to the concerned colleges and the Department of Science and Technology for audit and approval, and last to the Department of Personnel for implementation. Scientific research funds shall not be used for purposes irrelevant to the applied scientific researches. When using up the funds, applicants are required to make a written summary, and fill in "Conclusive Report on Anhui Agricultural University Introduced High-level Talents'Sponsored Research Project", which is subject to the review by the Department of Personnel and other relevant functional departments.
3. AAU exercises position-goal administration over the high-level personnel, which requires the employing units to establish and perfect the introduced talents'academic archives to keep a good track of their work in progress. The Department of Personnel, in conjunction with those relevant units, shall carry out evaluations of the introduced talents’ performance, such as mid-term examination of their work when they have worked in AAU for three years, and final examination at the end of their service etc. AAU shall continue to employ those recognized to be up to the agreed requirements, or else, shall conditionally reduce their benefits and even dismiss them in line with AAU’s relevant provisions of posts management.
VI. Ways of Talents Introduction 
While vigorously highlighting rigid introduction of talents, AAU shall actively carry out flexible introduction. AS for those high-level talents (domestic or foreign) hard for quick rigid introduction, we take the policy of "not taking possession, but taking advantages", encouraging them to take flexible flow-ways to work in AAU as honorary professors,  part-time professors or visiting professors, to do consulting, lecturing or researches. We also allow the introduced talents to do long-term, short-term or periodic research work according to their actual situations.
VII. AAU’s recruitment has no closing date for urgently needed special talents.
VIII. The Measures shall come into effect since the date of issuance. The original “Measures of Anhui Agricultural University High-level Talents Introduction"(AAU Personnel [2010] No.21) shall be repealed on the same date, but the agreements signed on its principle shall continue to be effective.
IX. AAU’s Department of Personnel is responsible for the interpretation of the new Measures.

